# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorRahayal2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah and Garret made their way through the forest."
    new "Sarah and Garret made their way through the forest."

    old "With the spirit seemingly subdued, it felt as if all of the forest had become more calm."
    new "With the spirit seemingly subdued, it felt as if all of the forest had become more calm."

    old "Sarah relied on Garret's tracking skills to lead them back to civilization."
    new "Sarah relied on Garret's tracking skills to lead them back to civilization."

    old "Whatever else she could say of him, he was most certainly a skilled Huntsman."
    new "Whatever else she could say of him, he was most certainly a skilled Huntsman."

    old "She did her best to try and process everything that had happened."
    new "She did her best to try and process everything that had happened."

    old "What will you tell them?"
    new "What will you tell them?"

    old "Tell who?"
    new "Tell who?"

    old "The Mayor...the townsfolk?"
    new "The Mayor...the townsfolk?"

    old "I'll give them one of the pelts that we have in storage, we have a few belonging to rather large bears."
    new "I'll give them one of the pelts that we have in storage, we have a few belonging to rather large bears."

    old "They'll never believe that. They saw the creature, they-"
    new "They'll never believe that. They saw the creature, they-"

    old "They saw the creature, sure, but who did really?"
    new "They saw the creature, sure, but who did really?"

    old "A few farmers here and there."
    new "A few farmers here and there."

    old "I'll give them the pelt and tell them the beast is dead."
    new "I'll give them the pelt and tell them the beast is dead."

    old "There will never be another attack, and in a few years, this will all just be an aweful story people tell."
    new "There will never be another attack, and in a few years, this will all just be an aweful story people tell."

    old "It's you I'm more worried about."
    new "It's you I'm more worried about."

    old "They might forget...but I'm afraid you won't."
    new "They might forget...but I'm afraid you won't."

    old "Perhaps...it will be a while before I can..."
    new "Perhaps...it will be a while before I can..."

    old "Forgive yourself? I told you, it wasn't your fault, the curse-"
    new "Forgive yourself? I told you, it wasn't your fault, the curse-"

    old "But there is a difference between knowing something and believing it."
    new "But there is a difference between knowing something and believing it."

    old "Sarah nodded, but said nothing."
    new "Sarah nodded, but said nothing."

    old "She knew he was right about that."
    new "She knew he was right about that."

    old "Together the two made their way through the forest, back to town."
    new "Together the two made their way through the forest, back to town."

    old "Sarah did as she said, settling up with the Mayor, who seemed almost eager to believe her."
    new "Sarah did as she said, settling up with the Mayor, who seemed almost eager to believe her."

    old "As for Garret, she knew she would worry about him for a long time to come."
    new "As for Garret, she knew she would worry about him for a long time to come."

    old "Early next day, Sarah's army set out back to Rahayal."
    new "Early next day, Sarah's army set out back to Rahayal."

    old "The swift progress they made continued for days, as if they moved under a divine wind."
    new "The swift progress they made continued for days, as if they moved under a divine wind."

    old "Before long, the gates of Lethram appeared before them."
    new "Before long, the gates of Lethram appeared before them."

    old "Arriving at the port city, they equally found their fortune to favor them."
    new "Arriving at the port city, they equally found their fortune to favor them."

    old "Lady Carolyn had chartered all the ships they might need, and over stable waters, it carried them from Lethram to Rahayal."
    new "Lady Carolyn had chartered all the ships they might need, and over stable waters, it carried them from Lethram to Rahayal."

    old "So vast their army, so vast their fleet, no bandit or pirate dared to even hint at attacking them."
    new "So vast their army, so vast their fleet, no bandit or pirate dared to even hint at attacking them."

    old "And so, they arrived, unmolested, at mighty Rahayal."
    new "And so, they arrived, unmolested, at mighty Rahayal."

    old "The city that knew no equal in the world."
    new "The city that knew no equal in the world."

    old "Standing at the helm of her ship, Sarah spotted the great city by the landmark that defined it."
    new "Standing at the helm of her ship, Sarah spotted the great city by the landmark that defined it."

    old "The Great Black Pyramid."
    new "The Great Black Pyramid."

    old "The building that housed the Eternal Court, the center of all political power in the Empire."
    new "The building that housed the Eternal Court, the center of all political power in the Empire."

    old "The spider at the center of a vast web."
    new "The spider at the center of a vast web."

    old "Her own army was flanked by the Mithran forces that had marched with them all the way from beyond Bagrad."
    new "Her own army was flanked by the Mithran forces that had marched with them all the way from beyond Bagrad."

    old "Together, they made for an imposing force as they marched down the broad walkways of the city."
    new "Together, they made for an imposing force as they marched down the broad walkways of the city."

    old "Rahayal, the vast capital, was no stranger to extravagance and shows of force."
    new "Rahayal, the vast capital, was no stranger to extravagance and shows of force."

    old "It took a lot to make the citizens take notice of anything in particular, but this, they took note of."
    new "It took a lot to make the citizens take notice of anything in particular, but this, they took note of."

    old "A legion returning home. A strange army among them."
    new "A legion returning home. A strange army among them."

    old "The city would be buzzing with a dozen rumors, half true and half false, before the sun had set."
    new "The city would be buzzing with a dozen rumors, half true and half false, before the sun had set."

    old "As she marched among her soldiers, Sarah took in the city of Rahayal."
    new "As she marched among her soldiers, Sarah took in the city of Rahayal."

    old "Despite all the turns of her life, she had never before seen it."
    new "Despite all the turns of her life, she had never before seen it."

    old "And the city was unlike any other."
    new "And the city was unlike any other."

    old "The memories of her old home in Rosanna came back to her."
    new "The memories of her old home in Rosanna came back to her."

    old "Once, when she had been younger, she had imagined that all the cities of the world were like that."
    new "Once, when she had been younger, she had imagined that all the cities of the world were like that."

    old "But the more she saw of the world, the more she realized how small her home had been. How vast the world beyond her own horizons."
    new "But the more she saw of the world, the more she realized how small her home had been. How vast the world beyond her own horizons."

    old "The armies continued their march through the city, gathering onlookers as they went."
    new "The armies continued their march through the city, gathering onlookers as they went."

    old "Finally, Sarah and her forces arrived at Lady Carolyn's private estate."
    new "Finally, Sarah and her forces arrived at Lady Carolyn's private estate."

    old "Anywhere else in the world, it would have been an impressive sight."
    new "Anywhere else in the world, it would have been an impressive sight."

    old "Here the estate sat among many others, larger and smaller."
    new "Here the estate sat among many others, larger and smaller."

    old "In the context of the city, the estate almost appeared modest."
    new "In the context of the city, the estate almost appeared modest."

    old "It takes about a dozen servants, just to keep the whole thing from falling apart."
    new "It takes about a dozen servants, just to keep the whole thing from falling apart."

    old "Sarah looked at Lady Carolyn."
    new "Sarah looked at Lady Carolyn."

    old "That many?"
    new "That many?"

    old "And with you and all your other guests, I've even had to increase the staff beyond that."
    new "And with you and all your other guests, I've even had to increase the staff beyond that."

    old "How...do you even pay for all that?"
    new "How...do you even pay for all that?"

    old "Many noble families were ruined after the fall of Rosanna."
    new "Many noble families were ruined after the fall of Rosanna."

    old "Their wealth was in lands, farms and mines."
    new "Their wealth was in lands, farms and mines."

    old "When the hordes of the Tribes came, there was little more than some gems and gold that they could smuggle."
    new "When the hordes of the Tribes came, there was little more than some gems and gold that they could smuggle."

    old "And you can't eat gold or gems."
    new "And you can't eat gold or gems."

    old "So they were all eager to sell their belongings for money."
    new "So they were all eager to sell their belongings for money."

    old "But the merchants of Rahayal are no fools. They saw how desperate the nobles were."
    new "But the merchants of Rahayal are no fools. They saw how desperate the nobles were."

    old "Most sold their already diminished belongings for less than a third of what they were worth."
    new "Most sold their already diminished belongings for less than a third of what they were worth."

    old "Lady Carolyn looked out across the sprawling gardens of the estate."
    new "Lady Carolyn looked out across the sprawling gardens of the estate."

    old "But my family has always made its money in banking."
    new "But my family has always made its money in banking."

    old "So while we lost some in the fall, most of our assets had been diversified, and we already held sizeable holdings in Rahayal."
    new "So while we lost some in the fall, most of our assets had been diversified, and we already held sizeable holdings in Rahayal."

    old "In the end, I was better protected from the losses than most."
    new "In the end, I was better protected from the losses than most."

    old "Sarah watched as Lady Carolyn calmly explained all of it. Almost without emotion."
    new "Sarah watched as Lady Carolyn calmly explained all of it. Almost without emotion."

    old "Then again, she had never been a woman much prone to emotion."
    new "Then again, she had never been a woman much prone to emotion."

    old "So you're one of the lucky ones?"
    new "So you're one of the lucky ones?"

    old "That, and my connections to Gilead have managed to make sure that I can afford to maintain a place like this."
    new "That, and my connections to Gilead have managed to make sure that I can afford to maintain a place like this."

    old "Many of the other nobles were less fortunate."
    new "Many of the other nobles were less fortunate."

    old "Honestly, part of it was their own fault."
    new "Honestly, part of it was their own fault."

    old "So many of them imagined that the fall of Rosanna was a temporary thing."
    new "So many of them imagined that the fall of Rosanna was a temporary thing."

    old "They kept living as if they would return home to their holdings in a few months."
    new "They kept living as if they would return home to their holdings in a few months."

    old "So their money ran out quickly."
    new "So their money ran out quickly."

    old "The common folk, by contrast, were smarter. They always knew they had to work for their money."
    new "The common folk, by contrast, were smarter. They always knew they had to work for their money."

    old "Working here in Rahayal or working in Rosanna, it was all much the same to them."
    new "Working here in Rahayal or working in Rosanna, it was all much the same to them."

    old "But please, don't let me bore you with all this history."
    new "But please, don't let me bore you with all this history."

    old "Go and make yourself at home first."
    new "Go and make yourself at home first."

    old "We can have dinner later tonight."
    new "We can have dinner later tonight."

    old "It's been a long journey, I look forward to taking a moment to myself."
    new "It's been a long journey, I look forward to taking a moment to myself."

    old "Lady Carolny nodded."
    new "Lady Carolny nodded."

    old "I have had the servants prepare the best room for you."
    new "I have had the servants prepare the best room for you."

    old "Also, the servant quarters have been converted into improvised baracks for your soldiers."
    new "Also, the servant quarters have been converted into improvised baracks for your soldiers."

    old "And your most trusted friends will of course been seen to as well, each a room fitting of their station."
    new "And your most trusted friends will of course been seen to as well, each a room fitting of their station."

    old "Sarah slightly bowed her head."
    new "Sarah slightly bowed her head."

    old "Thank you, Carolyn."
    new "Thank you, Carolyn."

    old "Your help means a lot to me."
    new "Your help means a lot to me."

    old "Carolyn grabbed her hand and squeezed it."
    new "Carolyn grabbed her hand and squeezed it."

    old "It means nothing, dear."
    new "It means nothing, dear."

    old "If together, we can restore our homeland, all of this will have been worth it a hundred times over."
    new "If together, we can restore our homeland, all of this will have been worth it a hundred times over."

    old "Now go, settle in."
    new "Now go, settle in."

    old "We will speak later tonight."
    new "We will speak later tonight."

    old "Servants rushed over to gather her belongings and carried them away."
    new "Servants rushed over to gather her belongings and carried them away."

    old "Nervously, Sarah followed them into the estate."
    new "Nervously, Sarah followed them into the estate."

    old "The abundance of wealth was on display everywhere."
    new "The abundance of wealth was on display everywhere."

    old "Sarah was still dazzling from the sight of it when she finally came upon her own room."
    new "Sarah was still dazzling from the sight of it when she finally came upon her own room."

    old "Just as promised, it was fit for royalty."
    new "Just as promised, it was fit for royalty."

    old "Sarah had lived on the road for years now. She could sleep as easily in an open field as anywhere else."
    new "Sarah had lived on the road for years now. She could sleep as easily in an open field as anywhere else."

    old "A room like this seemed almost obscene to her now."
    new "A room like this seemed almost obscene to her now."

    old "She had to laugh as she walked through it."
    new "She had to laugh as she walked through it."

    old "Had this not been most of her youth? Growing up in a castle, rooms like these, servants to answer any request?"
    new "Had this not been most of her youth? Growing up in a castle, rooms like these, servants to answer any request?"

    old "Sarah ran her hands across the silk sheets on the bed."
    new "Sarah ran her hands across the silk sheets on the bed."

    old "Then why did it all now feel so alien to her?"
    new "Then why did it all now feel so alien to her?"

    old "Why did it feel like this was happening to someone else?"
    new "Why did it feel like this was happening to someone else?"

    old "Across the other side of the room, large glass doors had been slightly opened."
    new "Across the other side of the room, large glass doors had been slightly opened."

    old "A soft wind played with the translucent curtains."
    new "A soft wind played with the translucent curtains."

    old "Sarah walked towards it."
    new "Sarah walked towards it."

    old "As she walked through the doors, she stepped out onto the balcony."
    new "As she walked through the doors, she stepped out onto the balcony."

    old "A sprawling sight of the city, extending endlessly until the horizon and probably beyond."
    new "A sprawling sight of the city, extending endlessly until the horizon and probably beyond."

    old "The size of it all was so overwhelming, that Sarah could not help but stare."
    new "The size of it all was so overwhelming, that Sarah could not help but stare."

    old "A wind was coming in from the ocean, rushing across her face. Cool air and the smell of salt."
    new "A wind was coming in from the ocean, rushing across her face. Cool air and the smell of salt."

    old "Closing her eyes, Sarah could see it all as clearly as when she opened her eyes."
    new "Closing her eyes, Sarah could see it all as clearly as when she opened her eyes."

    old "And for a moment, she simply existed."
    new "And for a moment, she simply existed."

    old "Taking in the strangeness of how her life had ended up as it had."
    new "Taking in the strangeness of how her life had ended up as it had."

    old "How she had come to find her way here."
    new "How she had come to find her way here."

    old "When she opened her eyes again, she found the city, same as it had been before."
    new "When she opened her eyes again, she found the city, same as it had been before."

    old "Vast. Sprawling."
    new "Vast. Sprawling."

    old "Could it be true, what Lady Carolyn had said?"
    new "Could it be true, what Lady Carolyn had said?"

    old "Could this Gilead figure give her the armies she need to retake her homeland?"
    new "Could this Gilead figure give her the armies she need to retake her homeland?"

    old "For so many years, memories of her home had haunted her."
    new "For so many years, memories of her home had haunted her."

    old "They had become only painful reminders of what she had lost."
    new "They had become only painful reminders of what she had lost."

    old "Now, for the first time in years, Sarah dreamed that she might actually see her home again."
    new "Now, for the first time in years, Sarah dreamed that she might actually see her home again."

    old "See it restored."
    new "See it restored."

    old "Sarah gripped the railing of the balcony for balance."
    new "Sarah gripped the railing of the balcony for balance."

    old "The world turned about her, as if she stood in the center of a great hurricane."
    new "The world turned about her, as if she stood in the center of a great hurricane."

    old "What should I do?"
    new "What should I do?"

    old "Her questions drifted away on the wind, out across a city, that offered no answer."
    new "Her questions drifted away on the wind, out across a city, that offered no answer."

    old "It was a few hours later when a knock at the door finally awakened Sarah from her solemn thoughts."
    new "It was a few hours later when a knock at the door finally awakened Sarah from her solemn thoughts."

    old "A servant, a young woman, entered the room. Her eyes fixed to the floor."
    new "A servant, a young woman, entered the room. Her eyes fixed to the floor."

    old "Your Highness, Lady Carolyn has invited you to join her in the dining room."
    new "Your Highness, Lady Carolyn has invited you to join her in the dining room."

    old "Of course. Can you escort me there?"
    new "Of course. Can you escort me there?"

    old "The young woman nodded."
    new "The young woman nodded."

    old "Yes, your Highness, but Lady Carolyn has also extended a gift to you."
    new "Yes, your Highness, but Lady Carolyn has also extended a gift to you."

    old "The young woman gestured towards the bed."
    new "The young woman gestured towards the bed."

    old "A dress was sprawled out across it. Just by looking at it, one could see how expensive it was."
    new "A dress was sprawled out across it. Just by looking at it, one could see how expensive it was."

    old "I don't understand."
    new "I don't understand."

    old "Lady Carolyn has gifted you this dress for tonight's event."
    new "Lady Carolyn has gifted you this dress for tonight's event."

    old "It was handmade by one of the finest tailors in the Weaving district."
    new "It was handmade by one of the finest tailors in the Weaving district."

    old "Sarah looked at the dress."
    new "Sarah looked at the dress."

    old "It had been years since she wore anything like this."
    new "It had been years since she wore anything like this."

    old "Wear the dress"
    new "Wear the dress"

    old "Thank you for bringing me this..."
    new "Thank you for bringing me this..."

    old "Sarah awkwardly looked at the dress."
    new "Sarah awkwardly looked at the dress."

    old "Gods, how did one even put one of these one."
    new "Gods, how did one even put one of these one."

    old "Would you...mind helping me?"
    new "Would you...mind helping me?"

    old "The servant girl nodded."
    new "The servant girl nodded."

    old "The servant girl rushed over and began to help Sarah undo her armor."
    new "The servant girl rushed over and began to help Sarah undo her armor."

    old "Piece by piece, the solid metal clattered to the floor and rested there."
    new "Piece by piece, the solid metal clattered to the floor and rested there."

    old "The young woman pulled away the last pieces and added them to the rest."
    new "The young woman pulled away the last pieces and added them to the rest."

    old "Standing in her lingerie, Sarah felt the cold air run past her body."
    new "Standing in her lingerie, Sarah felt the cold air run past her body."

    old "The servant girl grabbed the dress and began to help Sarah put it on."
    new "The servant girl grabbed the dress and began to help Sarah put it on."

    old "Once, this had been normal to her."
    new "Once, this had been normal to her."

    old "Now, Sarah wondered more than ever, what had happened."
    new "Now, Sarah wondered more than ever, what had happened."

    old "Had her younger self been a fool? Or had she herself grown strange to the world?"
    new "Had her younger self been a fool? Or had she herself grown strange to the world?"

    old "With some help from the servant girl, Sarah finally managed to put the dress on."
    new "With some help from the servant girl, Sarah finally managed to put the dress on."

    old "Sarah looked at herself in the giant mirror in her room."
    new "Sarah looked at herself in the giant mirror in her room."

    old "The dress was perfect."
    new "The dress was perfect."

    old "Far from the style that she had grown up wearing in Rosanna, but undoubtedly a work of art."
    new "Far from the style that she had grown up wearing in Rosanna, but undoubtedly a work of art."

    old "How strange, she thought, to again be wearing something like this."
    new "How strange, she thought, to again be wearing something like this."

    old "Sarah nervously looked about."
    new "Sarah nervously looked about."

    old "How...does it look?"
    new "How...does it look?"

    old "The servant girl flashed a brief smile."
    new "The servant girl flashed a brief smile."

    old "You're beautiful, my Lady. The dress fits you perfectly."
    new "You're beautiful, my Lady. The dress fits you perfectly."

    old "Please, take me to the dining room."
    new "Please, take me to the dining room."

    old "Keep on your armor"
    new "Keep on your armor"

    old "My armor will suit me fine."
    new "My armor will suit me fine."

    old "Following the servant girl, Sarah made her way through the stretching halls of the estate."
    new "Following the servant girl, Sarah made her way through the stretching halls of the estate."

    old "The young woman didn't appear very talkative."
    new "The young woman didn't appear very talkative."

    old "Sarah arrived at the massive dining room."
    new "Sarah arrived at the massive dining room."

    old "She could see Lady Carolyn already waiting for her."
    new "She could see Lady Carolyn already waiting for her."

    old "Aah, welcome Sarah."
    new "Aah, welcome Sarah."

    old "Sarah saw Carolyn study her dress."
    new "Sarah saw Carolyn study her dress."

    old "I'm glad to see you liked my gift."
    new "I'm glad to see you liked my gift."

    old "Thank you, it's really beautiful."
    new "Thank you, it's really beautiful."

    old "Had it made to fit your exact measurements."
    new "Had it made to fit your exact measurements."

    old "Sarah wasn't sure she wanted to know how Lady Carolyn managed to get those."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure she wanted to know how Lady Carolyn managed to get those."

    old "Sarah saw Lady Carolyn's eyes run up and down her body."
    new "Sarah saw Lady Carolyn's eyes run up and down her body."

    old "Was there something wrong with the dress?"
    new "Was there something wrong with the dress?"

    old "I just don't think those types of clothes really fit me anymore."
    new "I just don't think those types of clothes really fit me anymore."

    old "Lady Carolyn raised only a single eyebrow."
    new "Lady Carolyn raised only a single eyebrow."

    old "My mistake then."
    new "My mistake then."

    old "Lady Carolyn gestured at the chair opposite of her."
    new "Lady Carolyn gestured at the chair opposite of her."

    old "Have a seat."
    new "Have a seat."

    old "Sarah sat down opposite of Lady Carolyn."
    new "Sarah sat down opposite of Lady Carolyn."

    old "My chef here is a delight. I don't think even Castle Reinmeer had one like him."
    new "My chef here is a delight. I don't think even Castle Reinmeer had one like him."

    old "Sarah looked at the plate in front of her, the first meal already served."
    new "Sarah looked at the plate in front of her, the first meal already served."

    old "Then she looked up at Lady Carolyn."
    new "Then she looked up at Lady Carolyn."

    old "I didn't exactly come here for the food."
    new "I didn't exactly come here for the food."

    old "She saw a smile creep on Lady Carolyn's face."
    new "She saw a smile creep on Lady Carolyn's face."

    old "You know, dear, I used to think you were a bit dull, but you've grown a lot in your years of absence."
    new "You know, dear, I used to think you were a bit dull, but you've grown a lot in your years of absence."

    old "But you're right. Let's get to the point."
    new "But you're right. Let's get to the point."

    old "Lady Carolyn pushed a few papers across the table."
    new "Lady Carolyn pushed a few papers across the table."

    old "Ever since the Fall, I have gone quite far in maintaining the old structures of Rosanna."
    new "Ever since the Fall, I have gone quite far in maintaining the old structures of Rosanna."

    old "Structures?"
    new "Structures?"

    old "I have kept the most important noble families provided for, made sure they did not become destitute."
    new "I have kept the most important noble families provided for, made sure they did not become destitute."

    old "I have employed most of the officers from the Rosannan army as guards in my estate."
    new "I have employed most of the officers from the Rosannan army as guards in my estate."

    old "And I have even made sure to cultivate connections with leaders among the common folk."
    new "And I have even made sure to cultivate connections with leaders among the common folk."

    old "I have the ear of all the most important people in Rosannan society, living in exile here in Rahayal."
    new "I have the ear of all the most important people in Rosannan society, living in exile here in Rahayal."

    old "You, my dear, are the final piece to the puzzle."
    new "You, my dear, are the final piece to the puzzle."

    old "A leader around whom everyone can gather."
    new "A leader around whom everyone can gather."

    old "It was true, whether she wanted to admit it or not."
    new "It was true, whether she wanted to admit it or not."

    old "Nobody had a more direct claim than herself to the throne."
    new "Nobody had a more direct claim than herself to the throne."

    old "Gilead has pledged two legions to support your claim."
    new "Gilead has pledged two legions to support your claim."

    old "Add those to your band of mercenaries, and you have an army that the Tribesmen cannot defeat."
    new "Add those to your band of mercenaries, and you have an army that the Tribesmen cannot defeat."

    old "Sarah looked over the papers which summed up many of the same points."
    new "Sarah looked over the papers which summed up many of the same points."

    old "And this Gilead..."
    new "And this Gilead..."

    old "Why would he offer such a thing?"
    new "Why would he offer such a thing?"

    old "The Mythran Empire is vast, and even inside of the Empire, it is divided against itself."
    new "The Mythran Empire is vast, and even inside of the Empire, it is divided against itself."

    old "Gilead is a man whose hour draws short. He seeks to become relevant again."
    new "Gilead is a man whose hour draws short. He seeks to become relevant again."

    old "So all of this is vanity for him?"
    new "So all of this is vanity for him?"

    old "Carolyn looked from side to side, as if to make sure the room was empty, except for them."
    new "Carolyn looked from side to side, as if to make sure the room was empty, except for them."

    old "Gilead is a Noctori, you know this much, yes?"
    new "Gilead is a Noctori, you know this much, yes?"

    old "Noctori were the elites of Rahayal society. The ones that controlled the machinery of Empire from their seat in the Eternal Court."
    new "Noctori were the elites of Rahayal society. The ones that controlled the machinery of Empire from their seat in the Eternal Court."

    old "The Noctori are different from you and I."
    new "The Noctori are different from you and I."

    old "Different?"
